
<ArticleTitle>Health and safety and the Human Rights Act 1998.</ArticleTitle>
<AbstractText>The Human Rights Act 1998 came into effect on 2 October 2000. The list of human rights now embodied in United Kingdom law reflects the ideas and values of our changing and developing society. As a dynamic document the act has parallels with the ideals found in health and safety law. This article looks at the act and considers its implications for employers with regard to existing health and safety law.</AbstractText>
